fields.name: Black Tea
fields.description: Black tea, also translated to red tea in various East Asian languages, is a type of tea that is more oxidized than other types
fields.taste: smoky, earthy, spicy, nutty, citrus, caramel, leather, fruity, and honey

fields.name: White Tea
fields.description: A style of tea that features young or minimally processed leaves of the Camellia sinensis plant
fields.taste: floral, fresh, fruity, with a hint of cucumber or melon.

fields.name: Assam Tea
fields.taste: The flavor can range from brisk, smokey, earthy, musky and strong to a lighter cup with chocolate, cocoa, or even sweet and spicy notes

fields.name: Darjeeling Tea
fields.color: ranging from golden yellow to orange to deep red.
fields.taste: musky-sweet tasting notes similar to muscat wine

fields.name: Keemun
fields.taste: smooth, fruity, malty, unsweetened cocoa

fields.name: Lapsang Souchong
fields.color: ranging from amber to caramel to deep red.
fields.taste: sweet, piney, smoky

fields.name: Dianhong Tea
fields.taste: sweet, floral, and honey-like, though tends to be stronger and more bitter than other red teas

fields.name: Sencha Tea
fields.description: A Japanese green tea prepared by infusing whole tea leaves in hot water.
fields.taste: fresh, herbal, or grassy flavor, which can have varying vegetal grassy notes depending on how long it is steeped.

fields.name: Matcha Tea
fields.description: A finely ground powder of specially grown and processed green tea leaves, traditionally consumed in East Asia.
fields.taste: vegetal grassy notes, natural sweet nuttiness, a touch of bitterness with a pleasant savory ending

fields.name: Bancha
fields.description: Tea that is harvested from the same tea tree as sencha grade, but it is plucked later than sencha is. Can be found in a number of forms such as roasted, unroasted, smoked, etc.
fields.taste: mild, earthy grassiness, with dry, toasty notes with less of a deeply vegetal, umami flavor

fields.name: Gyokuro
fields.description: A type of shaded green tea from Japan. It differs from the standard sencha (a classic unshaded green tea) in being grown under the shade rather than the full sun.
fields.color: ranging from light green to dark green
fields.taste: very full-bodied, with a taste reminiscent to seaweed and grasses, followed by an intense sweetness

fields.name: Kukicha
fields.description: A Japanese blend made of stems, stalks, and twigs. It is available as a green tea or in more oxidised processing
fields.taste: mildly nutty and slightly creamy sweet flavour

fields.name: Hojicha
fields.description: A Japanese green tea that is roasted in a porcelain pot over charcoal
fields.taste: naturally sweet taste and smoky flavor with distinct notes of cocoa

fields.name: Green Tea
fields.description: Made from unoxidized leaves, Green tea is one of the least processed types of tea, offering high levels of antioxidants.
fields.taste: sweet, bittersweet, nutty, vegetal, buttery, floral, fruity, oceanic

fields.name: Da Hong Pao
fields.description: A Wuyi rock tea grown in the Wuyi Mountains of Fujian Province, China
fields.taste: peaty and earthy notes with hints of stone fruit, brown sugar, and molasses

fields.name: Shui Jin Gui
fields.description: A Wuyi oolong tea from Mount Wuyi, Fujian, China
fields.taste: sweet, floral

fields.name: Tieguanyin
fields.description: A variety of oolong tea that was originated during the 19th century
fields.taste: roasted, nutty, creamy, fruity, toasty, honey, floral, fresh, vegetal and mineral

fields.name: Shui Xian
fields.description: Heavy Wuyi tea, the darkest of the dark oolongs from Wuyi.
fields.taste: Mellow and delicate, the liquid is rich and complicated, with lingering fragrance in mouth

fields.name: Tieluohan
fields.description: Grown on the cliffs of the Wuyi Mountains in China, Tieluohan is a light tea with high regards due to legends
fields.taste: strong robust taste with a little bitterness

fields.name: Huangjin Gui
fields.description: A premium variety of Chinese oolong tea named after the yellow golden color of its budding leaves and its unique flowery aroma
fields.taste: smooth sweet flavor with a rich slightly nutty after-taste

fields.name: Wulong (oolong) Tea
fields.description: A traditional semi-oxidized Chinese tea produced through a process including withering the plant under strong sun and oxidation before curling and twisting
fields.color: bright green or yellow, or dark amber and red
fields.taste: Similar to black tea, though varied oxidation levels results in widely varied tastes

fields.name: Dòng Dǐng
fields.description: An oolong tea from Taiwan which translates to "Frozen Summit" or "Icy Peak", and is the name of the mountain in Taiwan where the tea is cultivated
fields.color: dark, army-green color with slight hints of brown
fields.taste: Conatins nutty notes, along with a smooth caramel-like flavor

fields.name: Dongfang Meiren
fields.description: A heavily oxidized, non-roasted, tip-type oolong tea originating in Hsinchu County, Taiwan
fields.taste: bright reddish-orange

fields.name: Ruan Zhi Oolong
fields.description: Ruan Zhi, or "soft stem", is a variety of oolong tea developed by the Taiwan Tea Experiment Station
fields.taste: oily flowery taste, with cherry tones.

fields.name: Baozhong
fields.description: A lightly oxidized tea, twist shape, with floral notes, and usually not roasted
fields.color: mix of pale honey yellow and jade green, bright in color, and clear
fields.taste: grassy, floral notes and the taste of creamy green melon.

fields.name: Jin Xuan
fields.description: A variety of oolong tea developed in 1980
fields.taste: taste is light, creamy, and flowery and sometimes compared to milk

fields.name: Assam Smoked Oolong
fields.description: Assam Smoked Oolong is a highly unusual and rare oak smoked tea from Mothola Tea Estate in Assam.
fields.taste: oaky, smokey, sweet, malty, has notes of apricots and tobacco

fields.name: Baihoi Yinzhen
fields.description: A white tea made from only the top buds of the Camellia sinensis plant.
fields.taste: sweet, vegetal, and delicate

fields.name: Baimudan tea
fields.description: A type of white tea made from plucks each with one leaf shoot and two immediate young leaves (one bud two leaf ratio) of the Camellia sinensis plant.
fields.taste: toasty, slightly sweet floral notes and a clean aftertaste.

fields.name: Shoumei tea
fields.description: A type of white tea produced from naturally withered upper leafs and tips
fields.taste: sweet, vegetal, delicate

fields.description: A complex white tea from Fuding in Fujian Province
fields.taste: smooth, juicy taste has clean notes of unripe fruits, light wood and just a touch of vegetal astringency.

fields.name: Satemwa Antlers
fields.description: A white tea made from a blend of select Superior Cultivars from Malawi, making it rich in theanine and antioxidants.
fields.taste: delicate sweetness of apricot and lychee lingers on the pallet

fields.name: Earl Grey
fields.description: A tea blend which has been flavoured with oil of bergamot
fields.taste: smoky, earthy, spicy, nutty, citrus, caramel, leather, fruity, and honey

fields.name: Konacha
fields.description: A type of green tea, composed of the dust, tea buds and small leaves that are left behind after processing Gyokuro or Sencha
fields.taste: mild, sweet, and grassy flavor with bitter after taste

fields.name: English Breakfast tea
fields.description: a traditional blend of black teas from Assam, Ceylon, Keemun and Kenyan teas.
fields.taste: may be slightly sweet, bitter, or malty

fields.name: Masala Chai
fields.description: An Indian tea beverage made by boiling black tea in milk and water with a mixture of aromatic herbs and spices
fields.taste: fragrant, spiced, astringent and a strong flavor

fields.name: Irish Breakfast
fields.description: A traditional blend of black teas from Assam and Ceylon teas. Because of its strength, it is most commonly served with milk.
fields.taste: Strong, malty, robust

fields.name: Russian Caravan
fields.description: A chinese tea blended with various oolong and black teas that gets its name from tea trading through a traderoute that connected eastern Asia to Europe through Russia
fields.taste: sweet, malty, and smoky taste

fields.name: Bai Jiguan
fields.description: A light Wuyi Mountain tea
fields.taste: starts off sweet, uniquely fruity with a toasty floral honeyed aroma and finishes with a lingering mellow fruit and honey note

fields.name: Genmaicha
fields.description: A Japanese brown rice green tea consisting of green tea mixed with roasted popped brown rice.
fields.taste: toasty, nutty

fields.name: Lady Grey
fields.description: Lady Grey tea is a trademarked variation on Earl Grey tea. Like Earl Grey, it is a black tea flavoured with bergamot essential oil.

fields.name: Jasmine Dragon Pearl
fields.description: Dragon Pearl Jasmine is comprised of little, hand-rolled pearls gently infused with jasmine flowers
fields.taste: Jasmine, root beer, sweet, but yet a light/subtle feeling.
